        "rendered": "Internationalization Functions"
    },
    "content": {
        "rendered": "\n<p>Check the <a href=\"https://developer.wordpress.org/apis/handbook/internationalization/internationalization-guidelines/\">Internationalization Guidelines</a> and learn what each i18n function is for, how to use them, and the best practices when writing your strings.</p>\n\n\n\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Basic functions</h2>\n\n\n\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\"><li><a href=\"https://developer.wordpress.org/reference/functions/__/\">__()</a></li><li><a href=\"https://developer.wordpress.org/reference/functions/_e/\">_e()</a></li><li><a href=\"https://developer.wordpress.org/reference/functions/_x/\">_x()</a></li><li><a href=\"https://developer.wordpress.org/reference/functions/_ex/\">_ex()</a></li><li><a href=\"https://developer.wordpress.org/reference/functions/_n/\">_n()</a></li><li><a href=\"https://developer.wordpress.org/reference/functions/_nx/\">_nx()</a></li><li><a href=\"https://developer.wordpress.org/reference/functions/_n_noop/\">_n_noop()</a></li><li><a href=\"https://developer.wordpress.org/reference/functions/_nx_noop/\">_nx_noop()</a></li><li><a href=\"https://developer.wordpress.org/reference/functions/translate_nooped_plural()/\">translate_nooped_plural()</a></li></ul>\n\n\n\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Translate &amp; Escape functions</h2>\n\n\n\n<p>Strings that require translation and is used in attributes of html tags must be escaped.</p>\n\n\n\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\"><li><a href=\"https://developer.wordpress.org/reference/functions/esc_html__/\">esc_html__()</a></li><li><a href=\"https://developer.wordpress.org/reference/functions/esc_html_e/\">esc_html_e()</a></li><li><a href=\"https://developer.wordpress.org/reference/functions/esc_html_x/\">esc_html_x()</a></li><li><a href=\"https://developer.wordpress.org/reference/functions/esc_attr__/\">esc_attr__()</a></li><li><a href=\"https://developer.wordpress.org/reference/functions/esc_attr_e/\">esc_attr_e()</a></li><li><a href=\"https://developer.wordpress.org/reference/functions/esc_attr_x/\">esc_attr_x()</a></li></ul>\n\n\n\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Date and number functions</h2>\n\n\n\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\"><li><a href=\"https://developer.wordpress.org/reference/functions/number_format_i18n\">number_format_i18n()</a></li><li><a href=\"https://developer.wordpress.org/reference/functions/date_i18n\">date_i18n()</a></li></ul>\n\n\n\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Functions also available in javascript</h2>\n\n\n\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\"><li><a href=\"https://developer.wordpress.org/reference/functions/__/\" rel=\"function\">__()</a> </li><li> <a href=\"https://developer.wordpress.org/reference/functions/_x/\" rel=\"function\">_x()</a> </li><li> <a href=\"https://developer.wordpress.org/reference/functions/_n/\" rel=\"function\">_n()</a> </li><li> <a href=\"https://developer.wordpress.org/reference/functions/_nx/\" rel=\"function\">_nx()</a> </li><li> sprintf()</li></ul>\n\n\n\n<p>Note: To be able to use these functions available in your javascript, you have to <a href=\"https://developer.wordpress.org/apis/handbook/internationalization/#internationalizing-javascript\">set up your plugin/theme javascript localization</a>.</p>\n",
        "protected": false
    },
